Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Pop the @butternut squash{300%grams}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast the butternut on the top shelf until golden and cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. When your water is boiling, stir the @macaroni{180%grams} into the pan and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While everything cooks, pick the @sage{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

== Bacon and Sage Crumb ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Stir-fry, ~{4-5%minutes}. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the sage leaves, @breadcrumbs{25%grams} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside your sage crumb. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

== Cheese Sauce ==

Melt the @butter{20%grams} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water{200%ml} a little at a time, followed by the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @Dijon mustard{10%grams}, grated Cheddar and @hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}(grated). Stir until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> Add less Dijon mustard if you prefer.

== Assembly ==

When the butternut is ready, remove it from the oven and turn your #grill{} on to high. Stir the bacon and butternut into the cheese sauce along with the cooked macaroni. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Transfer the pasta mixture to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the sage crumb, then pop it under the grill until golden and bubbling, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the butternut squash mac and cheese between your serving bowls and get stuck in. Enjoy!